task_description: Facing the building to your North (approx. 344°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: The current pitch (0°) may not capture the full height of the building; looking upward will reveal the roofline for accurate height estimation.
The current pitch (30° up) may not capture the full height; increasing pitch further will help reveal the building's roofline for accurate measurement.
The current 30° upward pitch still may not capture the building's full vertical extent; increasing pitch further will help confirm if the roofline is fully visible for height estimation.
The current 30° upward pitch still does not reveal the building's roofline; further upward rotation is necessary to capture the full vertical extent for height estimation.
The building's roofline remains unseen at 30° pitch; further upward rotation is required to capture the full vertical extent for height estimation.
The roofline remains obscured at 30° pitch; further upward rotation is necessary to capture the building's full height for estimation.

Since the roofline remains invisible even at maximum upward pitch, moving backward to increase distance may reduce the required viewing angle, allowing the building's full height to become visible within pitch limits.
